{"id": "EUVD-2023-59890", "enisaUuid": "bf2a9cd9-6615-30d2-9864-637f8d0ff876", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmd/raid10: fix leak of 'r10bio->remaining' for recovery\n\nraid10_sync_request() will add 'r10bio->remaining' for both rdev and\nreplacement rdev. However, if the read io fails, recovery_request_write()\nreturns without issuing the write io, in this case, end_sync_request()\nis only called once and 'remaining' is leaked, cause an io hang.\n\nFix the problem by decreasing 'remaining' according to if 'bio' and\n'repl_bio' is valid.", "datePublished": "2025-09-16T15:32:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-02T21:31:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cb827ed2bb34480dc102146d3a1f89fdbcafc028", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1d2c6c6e37fe5de11fd01a82badf03390e12df7a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8c5d5d7ffd1e76734811b8ea5417cf0432b9952c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1697fb124c6d6c5237e9cbd78890310154738084", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8d09065802c53cc938d162b62f6c4150b392c90e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/11141630f03efffdfe260b3582b2d93d38171b97", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3481dec5ecbbbbe44ab23e22c2b14bd65c644ec6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4f82e7e07cdaf2947d71968e3d6b73370a217093", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/26208a7cffd0c7cbf14237ccd20c7270b3ffeb7e", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53299"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53299"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "03aff109-47d8-305d-8173-8d2a5cb037cb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.180"}, {"id": "079a3f9f-32d9-314c-92dd-e3a5d3fec45f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "24afd80d99f80a79d8824d2805114b8b067e9823 <4f82e7e07cdaf2947d71968e3d6b73370a217093"}, {"id": "0dacaad8-1005-3c31-a0f2-5a7c6b32dc02", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "24afd80d99f80a79d8824d2805114b8b067e9823 <26208a7cffd0c7cbf14237ccd20c